<p>The picturesque island of Kish in the Persian Gulf was the venue of the 
TAFISA's first Certified Leadership Course in Sport for All. Delegates from ten 
Middle East countries namely Iraq, Lebanon, Afghanistan, Pakistan, Jordan, 
United Arab Emirates, Russia, Syria, Iran and Tajikistan attended this new 
worldwide program from August 27 to September 2, 2007. The event was hosted by 
the Iran National Olympic Committee, the National Olympic and Paralympic 
Academy, the National Sport for All Federation and Kish Free Zone Sports and 
Recreation Institute. Thanks to the outstanding efforts of TAFISA Iranian board 
member Mrs. Mitra Rouhi Dehkordi, the Leadership Course became a reality. TAFISA 
president Dr. Shang-Hi Rhee who paid a visit to the course welcomed the new 
initiative "as a milestone within the global Sport for All development".
The establishment of the Leadership Course is TAFISA's answer to meet an 
identified great demand from its members. As the result, the focus of the course 
is on leadership and management skills necessary for the development and 
promotion of Sport for All and physical activity on the national level and 
addresses Sport for All leaders from national sport organizations, NOCs, sport 
ministries etc. Major topics are policy, philosophy, volunteerism, marketing, 
management, programs, public health etc. in Sport for All given by renowned 
international experts in sport for All. 
<p>Participants who complete the course will be exposed to international 
perspectives, learn more about example programs and apply what they have learned 
in creative planning to meet future needs of their sport organizations. 
Participants that successfully complete the Course will receive a certificate 
from TAFISA. <p>The next two TAFISA Leadership Courses are to be held in Lagos/Nigeria, 
Nov. 26th – Dec. 2nd, 2007 for African countries and in 
Macau, Dec. 22nd –Dec. 28th, 2007 for Asian countries. The 
Courses will be hosted by Sports for All Nigeria and Macau Sports Development 
Board.
